@startuml 

title Webserver Slave Design / API Endpoints, example of security API endpoint (as seq diagram)

participant Website
participant DmxControllerHttpTask
participant HttpTask
participant ApiSecurity
participant SlaveTask
participant EspNowTask
participant NvsTask

Website -> DmxControllerHttpTask : POST Esp Now Key
DmxControllerHttpTask -> HttpTask : (Common API handler)
HttpTask -> ApiSecurity : Esp Now Key \n is for security
ApiSecurity -> SlaveTask : Handle Esp Now key
SlaveTask -> EspNowTask : Send to other nodes \n (for all nodes)
EspNowTask --> IEspNow : Send Esp Now message
IEspNow --> EspNowTask : Ack
EspNowTask --> SlaveTask: Ack
SlaveTask -> NvsTask : Store in NVS
NvsTask --> IEspNvs: Store in NVS
IEspNvs --> NvsTask: Ack
NvsTask --> SlaveTask : Ack
SlaveTask -> HttpTask : Respond to HTTP request
HttpTask --> DmxControllerHttpTask : Respond to \n HTTP request
DmxControllerHttpTask --> Website : Respond to \n HTTP request

@enduml 

